1 AN ACT concerning motor vehicles; relating to distinctive license plates;
2 providing for the FFA license distinctive plate.
3
4 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
5 Section 1. (a) On and after January 1, 2026, any owner or lessee of
6 one or more passenger vehicles or trucks registered for a gross weight of
7 20,000 pounds or less who is a resident of Kansas, upon compliance with
8 the provisions of this section, may be issued one FFA license plate for each
9 such passenger vehicle or truck. Such license plate shall be issued for the
10 same time as other license plates upon proper registration and payment of
11 the regular license fee as provided in K.S.A. 8-143, and amendments
12 thereto, and the payment to the county treasurer of the logo use royalty
13 payment.
14 (b) The Kansas FFA foundation may authorize the use of the
15 organization's logo to be affixed on license plates as provided by this
16 section. Any motor vehicle owner or lessee shall pay an amount of not less
17 than $25 nor more than $100, as determined by the Kansas FFA
18 foundation, as a logo use royalty payment for each such license plate to be
19 issued. The logo use royalty payment shall be paid to the county treasurer.
20 (c) Any applicant for a license plate authorized by this section may
21 make application for such license plate not less than 60 days prior to such
22 person's renewal of registration date, on a form prescribed and furnished
23 by the director of vehicles, and any applicant for such license plate shall
24 pay to the county treasurer the logo use royalty payment. Application for
25 registration of a passenger vehicle or truck and issuance of the license
26 plate under this section shall be made by the owner or lessee in a manner
27 prescribed by the director of vehicles upon forms furnished by the director.
28 (d) No registration or license plate issued under this section shall be
29 transferable to any other person.
30 (e) The director of vehicles may transfer a FFA license plate from a
31 leased vehicle to a purchased vehicle.
32 (f) Renewals of registration under this section shall be made annually,
33 upon payment of the fee prescribed in K.S.A. 8-143, and amendments
34 thereto, and in the manner prescribed in K.S.A. 8-132(b), and amendments

