1 thereto. No renewal of registration shall be made to any applicant until
2 such applicant provides to the county treasurer the annual royalty payment.
3 If such annual royalty payment is not made to the county treasurer, the
4 applicant shall be required to comply with the provisions of K.S.A. 8-143,
5 and amendments thereto, and return the license plate to the county
6 treasurer of such person's residence.
7 (g) The Kansas FFA foundation, with the approval of the director of
8 vehicles, shall design a plate to be issued under the provisions of this
9 section.
10 (h) As a condition of receiving the FFA license plate and any
11 subsequent registration renewal of such license plate, the applicant shall
12 consent to the division authorizing the division's release of motor vehicle
13 record information, including the applicant's name, address, royalty
14 payment amount, plate number and vehicle type to the Kansas FFA
15 foundation and the state treasurer.
16 (i) The collection and remittance of annual royalty payments by the
17 county treasurer shall be subject to the provisions of K.S.A. 8-1,141(h),
18 and amendments thereto.
19 Sec. 2. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
20 publication in the statute book.

